# Always commit changes

When you finish implementing a task that modified files in the repository, create a git commit before ending your response.

- Stage only the files related to the completed work
- Write a clear commit message describing what changed and why
- Do not push unless the user explicitly asks
- Do not commit secrets (.env, .env.local, credentials)
- If there is nothing to commit, say so instead of making an empty commit

The user expects the repo to stay in sync with the work you did.
